"{\"continue\":{\"rvcontinue\":\"20161123184148|751153397\",\"continue\":\"||\"},\"warnings\":{\"main\":{\"*\":\"Subscribe to the mediawiki-api-announce mailing list at <https://lists.wikimedia.org/mailman/listinfo/mediawiki-api-announce> for notice of API deprecations and breaking changes. Use [[Special:ApiFeatureUsage]] to see usage of deprecated features by your application.\"},\"revisions\":{\"*\":\"Because \\\"rvslots\\\" was not specified, a legacy format has been used for the output. This format is deprecated, and in the future the new format will always be used.\"}},\"query\":{\"normalized\":[{\"from\":\"John_Curtis_(American_politician)\",\"to\":\"John Curtis (American politician)\"}],\"pages\":{\"26929382\":{\"pageid\":26929382,\"ns\":0,\"title\":\"John Curtis (American politician)\",\"revisions\":[{\"timestamp\":\"2016-12-23T02:22:57Z\",\"contentformat\":\"text/x-wiki\",\"contentmodel\":\"wikitext\",\"*\":\"{{Infobox officeholder\\n|name= John R. Curtis\\n|image=File:John R Curtis.png\\n|imagesize=\\n|caption=\\n|order=\\n|office= Mayor of [[Provo, Utah]]\\n|term_start= January 5, 2010\\n|term_end=\\n|predecessor= [[Lewis K. Billings]]\\n|successor= \\n|birth_date= {{birth year and age|1960}}\\n|birth_place= [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]], U.S.\\n|death_date=\\n|death_place=\\n|party= \\n|alma_mater= [[Brigham Young University]] \\n|spouse= Sue Snarr\\n|children= 6\\n|religion= [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]]\\n|profession=\\n|residence= [[Provo, Utah|Provo]], Utah, U.S.\\n}}\\n\\n'''John R. Curtis''' (born 1960) is mayor of [[Provo, Utah]].<ref>[http://www.provo.org Provo City website].  Accessed April 19, 2013.</ref>\\n\\nCurtis attended high school at [[Skyline High School (Utah)]], where he met his future wife, Sue Snarr. He attended [[Brigham Young University]] and graduated with a degree in Business Management. He worked for OC Tanner and the Citizen Watch Company before taking a position as the COO of a Provo-based company, [[Action Target]] in 2000.\\n\\n==Political career==\\nJohn ran successfully for Mayor Provo City in 2009 defeating former legislator, Stephen Clark, with 53% of the vote and took office on January 5, 2010 on a platform of Safety, Prosperity, and Unity.\\n<ref>{{cite web | author= | title=Curtis wins Provo mayor race; incumbents tossed in some other races | url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705341959/Election-2009-Curtis-wins-Provo-mayor-race-incumbents-tossed-in-some-other-races.html?pg=all}}</ref>\\n<ref>{{cite web | author= | title=Meet Mayor Curtis | url=http://www.provo.org/government/mayor-s-office/meet-mayor-curtis | publisher=Provo City | year=2013 | accessdate=2013-12-12}}</ref> Since taking office he's been focused on Economic Development, revitalization of Downtown Provo, and getting a beach down at Utah Lake. John was re-elected for a second four-year term in 2013 with 86.49% of the vote.<ref>{{cite web|title=Curtis soars to victory and second term in Provo|url=http://www.heraldextra.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/elections/curtis-soars-to-victory-and-second-term-in-provo/article_54d3421f-84df-54eb-946d-3ca6c15562f8.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://universe.byu.edu/2013/11/06/provo-city-mayor-john-curtis-wins-re-election/|title=Provo City Mayor John Curtis wins re-election \\u2013 The Daily Universe|access-date=2016-05-18}}</ref>\\n\\n==Personal and Professional life==\\nHe is a member of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] and served a two-year mission in [[Taiwan]]. John and Sue have six children together.\\n\\nHe has also served on a number of community and advisory boards including the Provo/Orem Chamber of Commerce (now [[Utah Valley Chamber of Commerce]]), the Mountain Valley Chapter of the [[American Red Cross]], the [[Utah National Parks Council]] of the [[Boys Scouts of America]], and the Utah Valley Healthcare Foundation.\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist}}\\n\\n{{Utah cities and mayors of 100,000 population}}\\n\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Curtis, John R.}}\\n[[Category:1960 births]]\\n[[Category:Living people]]\\n[[Category:Mayors of places in Utah]]\\n[[Category:Brigham Young University alumni]]\\n[[Category:American Latter Day Saints]]\\n[[Category:American Mormon missionaries in Taiwan]]\\n[[Category:Politicians from Provo, Utah]]\\n[[Category:20th-century Mormon missionaries]]\\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\\n\\n\\n{{utah-politician-stub}}\"}]}}}}"